18:22.280 --> 18:29.600
Haldeman has been involved in two multi-book series, one called Atar the Merman and the other was Star Trek from the TV series.

18:30.080 --> 18:35.900
Although he enjoyed writing the first of his three Atar books, the ones that followed had nowhere to go to expand the characters.

18:35.900 --> 18:43.940
The publisher was banking on the current popularity of Dolphins and Whales, but the series never took hold and Haldeman's third book was never published.

18:44.680 --> 18:47.840
The Star Trek novels were a different sort of challenge, as Haldeman explains.

19:10.100 --> 19:21.540
I apologize for being like a vulture circling over the corpse, but I asked whether anybody was picking up Jim's work, and he said why don't you give it a try.

19:22.040 --> 19:35.580
Jim was taking the scripts from the TV show and just turning them into short stories, whereas they wanted me to do what Jim would have done if he had lived, which was a bright original novel around the Star Trek characters.

19:37.220 --> 19:44.580
Writing these novels was more than just sitting down and coming up with something for Spock, McCoy, and Kirk to do. Haldeman had to work out some other problems first.

20:24.940 --> 20:30.840
One of Haldeman's latest projects is a trilogy, of which the first book, Worlds, is already out.

20:31.100 --> 20:33.220
Haldeman gave us a little background on that novel.

20:38.800 --> 20:53.000
It's essentially the story of a woman who grew up, was born and grew up on a space colony, a space settlement, and is sent to Earth for a year of postgraduate work or finishing, if you want to call it that.

20:53.580 --> 21:03.380
Haldeman is being set up for a political position as a liaison between this world and Earth, and various strange things happened to her in the year that she's here.

21:27.080 --> 21:32.460
It seems as if a lot of authors are writing trilogies these days, and we wondered why Haldeman decided to write one.

21:34.720 --> 21:39.300
Well, it seems like an awfully big thing to put into one book.

21:41.060 --> 21:47.440
It looks as if each volume of the trilogy will be longer than any other book ever written.

21:48.660 --> 21:58.940
At least a third, each one so indeed, would have done, or nearly a half million words long, which are rather difficult to sell.

22:00.880 --> 22:14.060
And I just, you know, everybody's doing trilogies, so I can't idea what trilogy to do, it's part of it. They're very successful, second and third books have a built-in audience.

22:17.300 --> 22:19.020
Also, I wanted to try something big.

22:20.580 --> 22:31.940
And that's as good a reason as any. We've discussed in the previous sections of this interview that Haldeman's main concern is storytelling. He develops interesting characters and sets them in a believable scientific background.

